      <div style="flex: 1; min-width: 0;">
        <h4 class="research-paper-title">Structural Dynamics of Cooling Towers</h4>
        <p>
          My primary research investigates the dynamic behaviour of large-scale hyperbolic cooling towers under seismic and wind loading, with a focus
          on the <strong>Rooppur Nuclear Power Plant</strong>, Bangladesh's first nuclear power plant, situated near the seismically active Madhupur
          Fault.
        </p>
        <p>
          Using <strong>ABAQUS</strong>, I compared two column modelling strategies, <strong>Embedded Reinforcement</strong> and
          <strong>Simplified Timoshenko Beam</strong>, subjecting both to the 2001 Bhuj/Kachchh earthquake (non-linear time history) and wind loads
          via Greiner's equation (BNBC-2020).
        </p>
        <p style="font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--global-text-color-light);">
          <em>Published — Journal of Building Pathology and Rehabilitation, Springer, 2025</em>
        </p>
      </div>
