      <div style="flex: 1; min-width: 0;">
        <h4 class="research-paper-title">CFRP-Strengthened Beam-Column Steel Joints</h4>
        <p>
          This study investigates mild steel beam-column T-joints retrofitted with
          <strong>Carbon Fibre Reinforced Polymer (CFRP)</strong> under monotonic and cyclic loading, using ABAQUS FEA validated against experimental
          data.
        </p>
        <p>
          Three profiles, <strong>Square Hollow, I-Section</strong>, and <strong>Circular Hollow</strong>, were modelled with and without CFRP.
          Retrofitting improved load capacity by up to <strong>26.71%</strong> and energy dissipation by up to <strong>33.20%</strong> under cyclic
          loading.
        </p>
        <p style="font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--global-text-color-light);">
          <em>Under Review — Advances in Civil Engineering, 2025</em>
        </p>
      </div>
